Results.S:
At more caudal levels still , the SI dwindles , to give 
    space to the laterally expanding optic tract ( OT 
    ) ( Fig . lG , H ) .

Discussion.S:
Insular and ventral infralimbic cortex also project to 
    the nucleus of the solitary tract (Ross et al., '81; Saper, 
    '82a; Shipley, '82; Van der Kooy et al., '82; 
    Terrebeny and Neafsey, '831, and possibly to the 
    intermediolateral column of the spinal cord (Shipley, '82; 
    Shimada et al., '85).

References.S:
Koh (1978) Anatomical evidence of direct projections 
    from the nucleus of the solitary tract to the hypothalamus, 
    amygdala and other forebrain structures in the rat.
